verbs.description: delaminate (third-person singular simple present delaminates, present participle delaminating, simple past and past participle delaminated)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To cause (something assembled by lamination) to come apart into the layers that make it up.
(intransitive) To come apart into its component layers.
examples: Water damage caused the plywood of the floor to delaminate. The layers came apart and the whole piece had to be replaced.
